<descriptions>
  <description xml:lang="en" descriptionType="Abstract">GISTEMP is a dataset derived from the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Aadministration's (NOAA's) Global Historical Climatology Network (GHCN) and Extended Reconstructed Sea Surface Temperature (ERSST) datasets to explore temperature anomolies over the modern period of reliable temperature data collection, 1880-present. Temperature anomoly refers to the deviation from mean temperature over the 30 year period 1951-1980. GISTEMP v4 represents the 4th revision of the processes necessary to calculate these temperature anomolies. The first version of this dataset was created in 1981 by the now retired Dr. James E. Hansen. The project is currently led by Dr. Gavin Schmidt. GISTEMP is regularly updated to reflect the most recent completed month.</description>
</descriptions>
